Server


Topics
 go to bin/windows inside of kafka 
1. Create -> ./kafka-topics.bat --create --topic topic1 --partitions 3 --replication-factor 3 --bootstrap-server localhost:9092
2. list -> ./kafka-topics.bat --list --bootstrap-server localhost:9092
3. describe -> ./kafka-topics.bat --describe --bootstrap-server localhost:9092
4. delete -> ./kafka-topics.bat --delete --topic  topic1 --bootstrap-server localhost:9092 ( check config for delete.topic.enable = true)

Producer
1. producer send message -> ./kafka-console-producer.sh --bootstrap-server localhost:9092 --topic product-created-events-topic
2. producer send message with key -> ./kafka-console-producer.sh --bootstrap-server localhost:9092 --topic product-created-events-topic --property "parse.key=true" --property "key.seperator=:"


Consumer
1. from beginning -> ./kafka-console-consumer.sh --bootstrap-server localhost:9092 --topic product-created-events-topic --from-beginning
2. from beginning with key -> ./kafka-console-consumer.sh --bootstrap-server localhost:9092 --topic product-created-events-topic --from-beginning --property "print.key=true"
3. new messages -> ./kafka-console-consumer.sh --topic my-topic --bootstrap-server localhost:9092

to consume in order. producer has to send in unique key so that it will go to same partition